<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="2" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1560,2019]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,152,675]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="2" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis box="[199,326,1963,1986]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="393" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1963,1986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="393">Discussion</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Sivaruban &amp; Barathy &amp; Arunachalam &amp; Venkataraman &amp; Sivaramakrishnan, 2013" authorityName="Sivaruban &amp; Barathy &amp; Arunachalam &amp; Venkataraman &amp; Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="2013" box="[332,500,1963,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[332,500,1963,1986]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="393">Epeorus petersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[506,566,1963,1986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,566,1963,1986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="393" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from other Oriental species by the following combination of characters. Imago: (1) penes are not lobed apically, without lateral spine like processes and without short spines ventrally, (
<figureCitation box="[159,224,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,710,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-370@1.[151,1435,688,1822]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Imagos of E. petersi. 1–5, male imago: 1. Head; 2. Fore wing; 3. Hind wing; 4. Abdominal terga; 5. Genitalia (ventral view); 6. Female imago: abdominal terga." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268904/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); (2) longitudinal and cross veins of fore and hind wings reddish brown, all cross veins between costal and radial sector of fore wings surrounded with narrow, reddish brown clouds, apical of cells on costal and subcostal area of fore wings washed with dark brown; and apical of costal area of fore wings with about 15 slanting cross veins (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1347,218,241]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,710,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-370@1.[151,1435,688,1822]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Imagos of E. petersi. 1–5, male imago: 1. Head; 2. Fore wing; 3. Hind wing; 4. Abdominal terga; 5. Genitalia (ventral view); 6. Female imago: abdominal terga." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268904/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Larva: (1) abdominal terga yellowish brown, a pair of sub median bars in segment II–VIII, and a pair of sub median spines and a row of sparse setae on posterior margin of segment I–X (
<figureCitation box="[769,834,285,308]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–14" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1388,1411]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,466,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-428@2.[182,1408,451,1361]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–14. Epeorus petersi and Eperorus gilliesi, larvae. 7. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. petersi; 8. Gill I of E. petersi; 9. Gill VII of E. petersi; 10. Gill I of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 11. Gill VII of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 12. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 13. Leg of E. petersi; 14. Femur of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268906/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); (2) posterolateral spines on abdominal segment II–VII, progressively longer and curved inwards posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[737,804,318,341]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–14" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1388,1411]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,466,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-428@2.[182,1408,451,1361]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–14. Epeorus petersi and Eperorus gilliesi, larvae. 7. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. petersi; 8. Gill I of E. petersi; 9. Gill VII of E. petersi; 10. Gill I of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 11. Gill VII of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 12. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 13. Leg of E. petersi; 14. Femur of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268906/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); and (3) posterior edge of the lamellate portion of gill 1 bluntly pointed (
<figureCitation box="[328,392,352,375]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–14" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1388,1411]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,466,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-428@2.[182,1408,451,1361]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–14. Epeorus petersi and Eperorus gilliesi, larvae. 7. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. petersi; 8. Gill I of E. petersi; 9. Gill VII of E. petersi; 10. Gill I of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 11. Gill VII of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 12. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 13. Leg of E. petersi; 14. Femur of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268906/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,675]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">
There have been sporadic descriptions of species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1881" box="[779,870,385,408]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,870,385,408]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Epeorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[939,998,385,408]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">India</collectingCountry>
, especially from Himalayas (e.g. Eaton 1885; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapur, A. P. &amp; Kripalani, M. B." box="[218,483,418,441]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" pagination="183 - 221" refId="ref2587" refString="Kapur, A. P. &amp; Kripalani, M. B. (1963) The mayflies (Ephemeroptera) from the north - western Himalaya. Records of the Indian Museum, 59, 183 - 221." type="journal article" year="1963">Kapur &amp; Kripalani 1963</bibRefCitation>
). The only species from Western Ghats, 
<taxonomicName box="[915,1017,418,441]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Eperorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gilliesi">
<emphasis box="[915,1017,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">E. gilliesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Braasch, D." box="[1214,1377,418,441]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" pagination="117 - 118" refId="ref2415" refString="Braasch, D. (1981) Epeorus gilliesi new-species from India Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae). Reichenbachia, 19, 117 - 118." type="journal article" year="1981">Braasch (1981)</bibRefCitation>
from Khandala of the Northern Western Ghats, located in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[846,984,452,475]" country="India" name="Maharashtra" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Maharashtra</collectingRegion>
. Then, 
<bibRefCitation author="Braasch, D. &amp; Soldan, T." box="[1064,1339,452,475]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" pagination="131 - 134" refId="ref2524" refString="Braasch, D. &amp; Soldan, T. (1987) Neue Heptageniidae von Indien (Ephemeroptera). Reichenbachia, 24 (18), 131 - 134." type="journal article" year="1987">Braasch &amp; Soldan (1987)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from Southern Western Ghats, based on an immature larva from 
<collectingRegion box="[977,1052,485,508]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Kerala</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivaruban &amp; Barathy &amp; Arunachalam &amp; Venkataraman &amp; Sivaramakrishnan, 2013" authorityName="Sivaruban &amp; Barathy &amp; Arunachalam &amp; Venkataraman &amp; Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="2013" box="[1062,1232,485,508]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1062,1232,485,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Epeorus petersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1239,1300,485,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1239,1300,485,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is described from the Kumbakkarai stream, extending the range of this genus further down on the southern segment of the Western Ghats.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,675]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">
The larva of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivaruban &amp; Barathy &amp; Arunachalam &amp; Venkataraman &amp; Sivaramakrishnan, 2013" authorityName="Sivaruban &amp; Barathy &amp; Arunachalam &amp; Venkataraman &amp; Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="2013" box="[342,450,585,608]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[342,450,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">E. petersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[458,520,585,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[458,520,585,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
