<figureCitation box="[159,289,652,675]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–14" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1388,1411]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,466,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-428@2.[182,1408,451,1361]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–14. Epeorus petersi and Eperorus gilliesi, larvae. 7. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. petersi; 8. Gill I of E. petersi; 9. Gill VII of E. petersi; 10. Gill I of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 11. Gill VII of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 12. Dorsal view of abdomen of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981); 13. Leg of E. petersi; 14. Femur of E. gilliesi (after Braasch 1981)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268906/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Figs. 13, 14</figureCitation>
). The male imago of 
<taxonomicName box="[516,618,652,675]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Eperorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gilliesi">
<emphasis box="[516,618,652,675]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">E. gilliesi</emphasis>
